<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="325" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that the British and French Governments did not ask
                            exemplary damages on account of Nanchang riots.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>